Shirley Ballas (n√©e Rich; born 1960) is an English ballroom dancer, dance teacher, and dance adjudicator from Wallasey, Merseyside.
She specialises in the International Latin division, where she won several championship titles which earned her the nickname The Queen of Latin.
In 2017, Ballas became the head judge on the BBC TV show, Strictly Come Dancing, replacing Len Goodman.
